Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createRouteBlkAlongTrack(25.10)                createRouteBlkAlongTrack(25.10)

Name
       createRouteBlkAlongTrack  -  Creates routing blockages that are aligned
       to specified tracks which are in the shrunken row area

Syntax
        createRouteBlkAlongTrack

       [-help]

       -align_track <string>

       [-consider_cells_as_macros <string>]

       [-consider_macros_as_cells <string>]

       [-edge_shrink {<x y>}]

       -layer <string>

       [-no_cut_row]

       Creates routing blockages that are aligned to  specified  tracks  which
       are  in the shrunken row area. Use this command during partition floor-
       planning.

       Note:

              * Routing blockages are also created with  align  to  the  track
                which  is near to the shrunken row area with less than half of
                layer width.

              * Routing blockages honor rectilinear row area.

Parameters
       -align_track <string>
              Specifies the track layer to which the route blockages align to.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each createRouteBlkAlongTrack parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man createRouteBlkAlongTrack

       -consider_cells_as_macros <string>
              Specifies  the names of the cells that are considered as macros.
              Blockages are not created over them.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -consider_macros_as_cells <string>
              Specifies the names of the cells  that  are  considered  as  std
              cells. Blockages are created over them.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -edge_shrink {<x y>}
              Shrinks row area from the edge in X and Y direction.

              Data_type: point, optional

       -layer <string>
              Specifies  the name of the layer on which the tool creates rout-
              ing blockages for steam out.

              Data_type: string, required

       -no_cut_row
              Specifies whether the  blockages to be added should be based  on
              the no-cut row site area even if the row site area is not cut in
              the design.

              * Without  the -no_cut_row parameter, the tool will create route
                blockages based on the current row area. So the rows  for  ob-
                jects  like  insts, place blockages are expected to be cut out
                before running the createRouteBlkAlongTrack command to get ex-
                pected results.

              * With the -no_cut_row parameter, the  tool  will  identify  the
                rows have not been cut before and will call the cutRow command
                to  get  a cut row shape during the action. The route blockage
                is created based on the cut row shape. The  actual  row  shape
                will not be changed.

              * The  setFPlanMode  -no_cut_row  true  command has the same use
                with this option.

              Example:

              In the following illustration, the rows are not cut before. Now,
              without the -no_cut_row parameter, the tool will create a  route
              blockage  over  the  place  blockage  and  the  inst.  With  the
              -no_cut_row parameter, the tool will not create  route  blockage
              over them.

              Default: false

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The  following command creates a routing blockage on layer M2.
                The route blockages align to track layer M2:

                createRouteBlkAlongTrack    -layer    M2    -align_track    M3
                -edge_shrink {5 5}

